n kraljestev in de\u017eel zastopanih v dr\u017eavnem zboru,'' vol. 6: ''Kranjsko''. 1906. Vienna: C. Kr. Dvorna in Dr\u017eavna Tiskarna, p. 62.</ref>) is a village in the [[Municipality of \u0160kofja Loka]] in the [[Upper Carniola]] region of [[Slovenia]].\n\n==Church==\n[[File:Retece Slovenia - church.jpg|thumb|left|Saint John the Evangelist Church]]\nThe [[parish church]] in the settlement is dedicated to [[John the Evangelist]].<ref>[http://www.uradni-list.si/1/content?id=81743 Official Government Journal of the Republic of Slovenia, 30 July 2007, Declaration of the Church in Rete\u010de as a cultural monument]</ref> It was first mentioned in documents from 1501, but was rebuilt a number of times.<ref>[http://www.retece.com/zupnija Rete\u010de Parish website]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category-inline|Rete\u010de}}\n*[http://www.geopedia.si/Geopedia_en.html#L410_F10137608_b4_x451469_y113007_s15 Rete\u010de at Geopedia]\n\n{{\u0160kofja Loka}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Retece}}\n[[Category:Populated places in the Municipality of \u0160kofja Loka]]\n\n\n{{\u0160kofjaLoka-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Rete\u010de\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               =\n|settlement_type        = Village\n|motto                  =\n|image_skyline          = Retece Slovenia 2.jpg\n|imagesize              = 250px\n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             =\n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             =\n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           =\n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              =\n|mapsize                =\n|map_caption            =\n|image_map1             =\n|mapsize1               =\n|map_caption1           =\n|image_