{"title_page": "Return of the Cuckoo", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n  | show_name = Return of the Cuckoo<br />\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149\n  | image = Return of the Cuckoo (cover).jpg\n  | caption =''Return of the Cuckoo'' promo image\n  | genre = Modern drama\n  | creator = Chan Bo-Wah<br />Chan Bo-Yin<br />Man Kin-Fai<br />Ko Wai-Man\n  | starring = [[Julian Cheung]]<br />[[Charmaine Sheh]]<br />[[Nancy Sit]]<br />[[Steven Ma]]<br />[[Michael Tong]]\n  | narrated =\n  | theme_music_composer = Cho Kyu-man\n  | opentheme = \"Wishing Kwan Well\" by Julian Cheung\n  | endtheme = \"Cannot Forget\" by Steven Ma\n  | country = [[Hong Kong]]\n  | language = [[Cantonese]]\n  | num_seasons =\n  | num_episodes = 20\n  | list_episodes =\n  | executive_producer =\n  | producer = Tsui Yu-On\n  | location = {{MAC}}<br>{{HKG}}\n  | runtime = approx. 45 minutes (each)\n  | network = [[TVB]]\n  | picture_format =\n  | audio_format =\n  | first_aired = 10 July 2000\n  | last_aired = 4 August 2000\n  | related =\n  | website= http://tvcity.tvb.com/drama/moon/\n    }}\n'''''Return of the Cuckoo'''''  (Traditional Chinese: [[:zh:\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149|\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149]], literally \"The Moonlight at the 5th of October [Street]\", also known as \u6fb3\u9580\u8857, literally \"The Streets of Macao\") is a 20-episode [[TVB]] drama broadcast between July 2000 and August 2000. It was originally produced to be a [[sitcom]], however later edits made the production into a regular drama.\n\n==Synopsis==\nAs a child, Man Cho ([[Julian Cheung]]) was rendered mute as a result of the cruel actions of his mother and was adopted by the kind-hearted Ah Kiu ([[Nancy Sit]]). Man Cho grew up with Ah Kiu's daughter Kwan-Ho ([[Charmaine Sheh]]), and the two eventually develop romantic feelings for one another. Man Cho is extremely self-sacrificing, has an inferiority complex due to his disability, and therefore feels unworthy for Kwan-Ho. Ah Kiu is also against their relationship and things are further complicated when Szto Lai-Sun ([[Steven Ma]]) enters the picture after falling for Kwan-Ho too.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Julian Cheung]] as Man Cho \u6587\u521d (age 23)\n* [[Charmaine Sheh]] as Chuk Kwan-Ho \u795d\u541b\u597d (age 22)\n* [[Nancy Sit]] as Chu Sa-Kiu or Kiu Yee\n* [[Steven Ma]] as Szto Lai-Sun\n* [[Michael Tong]] as Kam Sing \u91d1\u52dd (age 25)\n* [[Sherming Yiu]] as Kong Yi-Man\n* [[Johnny Ngan]] as Chuen Hoi-King\n* [[Irene Wong]] as Wong Hoi-Lam\n\n==Sequel==\nThe [[Return of the Cuckoo (film)|movie version of '''''Return of the Cuckoo''''']] was released in the Fall of 2015. It is a continuation of the story where the drama left off.\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n'''[[TVB Anniversary Awards#2000|TVB Anniversary Awards]] (2000)'''\n* \"Favorite On-screen Partners\" (Julian Cheung and Charmaine Sheh &ndash; Man Chor and Chuk Kwan-Ho)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Julian Cheung &ndash; Man Chor)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Charmaine Sheh &ndash; Chuk Kwan-Ho)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Nancy Sit &ndash; Chu Sa-Kiu)\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Return Of The Cuckoo}}\n[[Category:TVB dramas]]\n[[Category:2000 Hong Kong television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000 Hong Kong television series endings]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n  | show_name = Return of the Cuckoo<br />\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149\n  | image = Return of the Cuckoo (cover).jpg\n  | caption =''Return of the Cuckoo'' promo image\n  | genre = Modern drama\n  | creator = Chan Bo-Wah<br />Chan Bo-Yin<br />Man Kin-Fai<br />Ko Wai-Man\n  | starring = [[Julian Cheung]]<br />[[Charmaine Sheh]]<br />[[Nancy Sit]]<br />[[Steven Ma]]<br />[[Michael Tong]]\n  | narrated =\n  | theme_music_composer = Cho Kyu-man\n  | opentheme = \"Wishing Kwan Well\" by Julian Cheung\n  | endtheme = \"Cannot Forget\" by Steven Ma\n  | country = [[Hong Kong]]\n  | language = [[Cantonese]]\n  | num_seasons =\n  | num_episodes = 20\n  | list_episodes =\n  | executive_producer =\n  | producer = Tsui Yu-On\n  | location = {{MAC}}<br>{{HKG}}\n  | runtime = approx. 45 minutes (each)\n  | network = [[TVB]]\n  | picture_format =\n  | audio_format =\n  | first_aired = 10 July 2000\n  | last_aired = 4 August 2000\n  | related =\n  | website= http://tvcity.tvb.com/drama/moon/\n    }}\n'''''Return of the Cuckoo'''''  (Traditional Chinese: [[:zh:\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149|\u5341\u6708\u521d\u4e94\u7684\u6708\u5149]], literally \"The Moonlight at the 5th of October [Street]\", also known as \u6fb3\u9580\u8857, literally \"The Streets of Macao\") is a 20-episode [[TVB]] drama broadcast between July 2000 and August 2000. It was originally produced to be a [[sitcom]], however later edits made the production into a regular drama.\n\n==Synopsis==\nAs a child, Man Cho ([[Julian Cheung]]) was rendered mute as a result of the cruel actions of his mother and was adopted by the kind-hearted Ah Kiu ([[Nancy Sit]]). Man Cho grew up with Ah Kiu's daughter Kwan-Ho ([[Charmaine Sheh]]), and the two eventually develop romantic feelings for one another. Man Cho is extremely self-sacrificing, has an inferiority complex due to his disability, and therefore feels unworthy for Kwan-Ho. Ah Kiu is also against their relationship and things are further complicated when Szto Lai-Sun ([[Steven Ma]]) enters the picture after falling for Kwan-Ho too.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Julian Cheung]] as Man Cho \u6587\u521d (age 23)\n* [[Charmaine Sheh]] as Chuk Kwan-Ho \u795d\u541b\u597d (age 22)\n* [[Nancy Sit]] as Chu Sa-Kiu or Kiu Yee\n* [[Steven Ma]] as Szto Lai-Sun\n* [[Michael Tong]] as Kam Sing \u91d1\u52dd (age 25)\n* [[Sherming Yiu]] as Kong Yi-Man\n* [[Johnny Ngan]] as Chuen Hoi-King\n* [[Irene Wong]] as Wong Hoi-Lam\n\n==Sequel==\nThe [[Return of the Cuckoo (film)|movie version of '''''Return of the Cuckoo''''']] was released in the Fall of 2015. It is a continuation of the story where the drama left off.\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n'''[[TVB Anniversary Awards#2000|TVB Anniversary Awards]] (2000)'''\n* \"Favorite On-screen Partners\" (Julian Cheung and Charmaine Sheh &ndash; Man Chor and Chuk Kwan-Ho)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Julian Cheung &ndash; Man Chor)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Charmaine Sheh &ndash; Chuk Kwan-Ho)\n* \"Top 10 Favorite Television Characters\" (Nancy Sit &ndash; Chu Sa-Kiu)\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Return Of The Cuckoo}}\n[[Category:TVB dramas]]\n[[Category:2000 Hong Kong television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2000 Hong Kong television series endings]]\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAwards and achievements:Update date format tag and add authority control template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Return_of_the_Cuckoo"}
